On December 6, 1865, the United States ratified the 13th Amendment to the Constitution, which abolished slavery in the country. This article reflects on the significance of this day and acknowledges the struggles endured by African Americans throughout history. It emphasizes the importance of continuing to work towards ending racism and building a society that respects all Americans. The article also pays tribute to those who suffered under slavery and calls for the protection of liberties and freedoms for future generations.